text: Oldflån-Ansätten Nature Reserve () is a nature reserve in Jämtland County in Sweden. The nature reserve includes the mountain peak Ansätten as well as areas of wetland. The wetland area is diverse in its composition and provides a habitat for several species of birds; its is part of the EU-wide Natura 2000-network and is a designated Ramsar site. The flora of the area is also rich and includes several species of orchids, cloudberry and Pedicularis oederi; the nature reserve is one of only a few known locales for the latter. The nature reserve is grazed by reindeer belonging to the local Sami population. ==References== Category:Nature reserves in Sweden Category:Natura 2000 in Sweden Category:Tourist attractions in Jämtland County Category:Geography of Jämtland County Category:Protected areas established in 2002 Category:2002 establishments in Sweden
